. This Korean species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1946" box="[727,864,1322,1348]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thorwaldi">
<emphasis box="[727,864,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. thorwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1050,1222,1323,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[1050,1222,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[298,496,1358,1384]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). It is very close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1976" box="[722,865,1358,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[722,865,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. planifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[936,1113,1358,1384]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
in morphology and genetics (
<figureCitation box="[159,259,1394,1420]" captionStart="FIGURE 149" captionStartId="236.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,198,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@236.[163,1425,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="236" captionText="FIGURE 149. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876861/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Figs 149</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[270,315,1394,1420]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876886/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">161</figureCitation>
). Although most of the known specimens can be identified by the characters given in the key, the two species may eventually be treated as local forms of the same species. Before synonymizing them, however, we still need more information about geographical variations and preferably also host plants and immature stages.
</paragraph>
